&lt;p&gt;All Regular Labs extensions with editor buttons, versions before 7 September 2018, cross site scripting (XSS):-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Articles Anywhere&lt;br /&gt;- Conditional Content&lt;br /&gt;- Dummy Content&lt;br /&gt;- Modals&lt;br /&gt;- Modules Anywhere&lt;br /&gt;- Sliders&lt;br /&gt;- Snippets&lt;br /&gt;- Tabs&lt;br /&gt;- Tooltips&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The editor button popup urls could potentially be used for cross site scripting (triggering custom javascript via the url). That is now fixed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;update notice: &lt;a href="https://www.regularlabs.com/component/content/article/1281-security-fix-7-sep-2018"&gt;https://www.regularlabs.com/component/content/article/1281-security-fix-7-sep-2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Versions numbers affected&lt;/h3&gt;
